Preheat the oven to 200C/180C/Gas 4.Put the peaches in an ovenproof dish and top with the butter.Bake in the oven for 20â€“25 minutes, until golden brown.To make the granola, combine the pecans, hazelnuts, coconut and cinnamon in a bowl. Make a well in the centre and add the honey, maple syrup and oil. Mix well.Spread the mixture on a baking tray and bake for 10 minutes. Stir the granola and bake for another 10 minutes, until golden brown. Remove from the oven and stir in the dried fruit.To serve, spoon the peaches into four bowls and top with the granola.